def: Sternness; severity. [Obs.]A Sara for goodness, a great Bellona for budgeness. Stanyhurst.
A kind of heavily built dished wheel with a long axle box, usedon gun carriages, usually having 14 spokes and 7 felloes; hence, awheel of similar construction for use on automobiles, etc.
Tint; color; tinge, See Tint. [Obs.]Time shall . . . embrown the teint. Dryden.
Derogatory.-- De*rog"a*tive*ly, adv. [R.] Sir T. Browne.
The quality of being perplexing; tendency to perplex. [Obs.]Dr. H. More.
